  "instructions": [
    "Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil and cook spaghetti until al dente, about 8-9 minutes.",
    "While pasta cooks, heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.",
    "Add minced garlic to the skillet, sauté until fragrant, about 30 seconds.",
    "Stir in confit tomatoes, oregano, and red pepper flakes, and simmer for 3 minutes.",
    "Drain the pasta and reserve 1/4 cup of pasta water.",
    "Toss the hot pasta with the tomato sauce, adding reserved pasta water as needed to coat.",
    "Sprinkle grated pecorino romano and chopped parsley over the pasta, and stir to combine.",
    "Season with salt and black pepper, serve immediately."
